&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and layout electronic schematics and PCBs (KiCad or Altium)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Select components, define stackups, and ensure manufacturability and serviceability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead mechanical and electrical integration with product and systems teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with suppliers for PCB fabrication, assembly, and production follow-up&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan and implement EMC mitigation and reliability strategies (ESD, surge, derating)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct board bring-up, debugging, and validation testing using standard lab tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create test plans, validation documentation, and track issue resolution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support development of embedded test firmware in collaboration with software teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Profile / Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6+ years of experience in electronic design for industrial, aerospace, or consumer products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in schematic design, PCB layout, and DFM/DFT principles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with EMC/EMI mitigation and validation testing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with microcontrollers (STM32 or similar) and communication buses (RS-485, I2C, SPI)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing EMS/SMT suppliers and prototype production&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to SSP 57000 requirements or similar aerospace standards is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical, documentation, and troubleshooting skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluent in English, French is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
