&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;As Senior Thermal and Fluidics Systems Engineer, you will be responsible for the design and engineering of Interstellar Lab’s controlled environment systems for plant growth. Your role focuses on air, water, nutrient, gas, and thermal regulation, translating biological requirements into robust, efficient, and scalable engineered systems. You will work closely with mechanical, electrical, and software teams to deliver integrated environmental control architectures, from early design through commissioning and operational optimization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and engineer controlled environment systems for plant growth, covering air, water, nutrients, and thermal regulation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engineer irrigation and fertigation systems including dosing, recirculation, filtration, and water treatment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design air handling and gas management systems for temperature, relative humidity, CO2, O2, and airflow control&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engineer thermal management for enclosures, canopy, and root zones&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform mass and energy balances for air, water, and nutrients at system level&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define sensors, actuators, and control strategies for environmental regulation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce P&amp;amp;IDs, sizing calculations, and technical specifications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support system integration, commissioning, testing, and performance optimization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
